# Samartha Ayurveda NFC Platform — User Manual

Welcome to the Samartha Ayurveda Smart NFC Business Card Platform. This manual provides step-by-step instructions for Administrators, Employees, and the process of programming physical NFC cards.

---

## 1. Administrator Guide

As an administrator, you have full control over the platform, including user management, gamification settings, broadcasting notices, and exporting analytics.

### 1.1 Logging In
1. Open your web browser and navigate to the platform URL (e.g., `http://127.0.0.1:5000`).
2. You will be redirected to the login page.
3. Enter the admin credentials:
   - **Username:** `admin`
   - **Password:** `admin123` (or your configured admin password)
4. Click **Sign In**. You will be taken to the Admin Dashboard.

### 1.2 System Health & Traffic Heatmap
- **System Health:** Provides a high-level overview of total users, active cards, total taps, and leads captured.
- **Traffic Heatmap:** Shows a visual breakdown of recent tap activity across all active cards.

### 1.3 User Control & Card Management
This section allows you to manage employee accounts and assign NFC cards.
1. Click **User Control** in the left sidebar.
2. You will see a list of all registered employees.
3. **Assigning a Card:** If an employee needs an NFC card, you can assign it here by linking a unique card ID to their account.
4. **Suspending/Pausing:** You can toggle an employee's status to "Terminated" or pause their card. If a card is paused, anyone tapping the physical card will see a "Card Paused" error page instead of the employee's profile.

### 1.4 Gamification: Daily Quests
Engage your employees by setting daily scan targets.
1. Under the **GAMIFICATION** section in the sidebar, click **Daily Quests**.
2. Select the **Date** for the quest (defaults to today).
3. Enter the **Target Unique Scans** (e.g., 20).
4. Enter a **Reward Description** (e.g., "Coffee Voucher").
5. Click **Save Goal**. The goal will now appear on all employees' dashboards.

### 1.5 Notice Board
Broadcast announcements to your team.
1. Click **Notice Board** in the sidebar.
2. Select the target recipient (e.g., "All Employees" or a specific user).
3. Type your announcement in the message box.
4. Click **Send Notice**. Employees will see this in their Inbox.

### 1.6 Export Data
Download platform analytics for reporting.
1. Click **Export Data**.
2. Choose your preferred format:
   - **Download Excel (.xlsx):** Generates a multi-sheet workbook containing raw tap logs and aggregated employee performance metrics.
   - **Download Tap Logs (.csv):** Generates a flat CSV file of all taps, useful for importing into BI tools.

---

## 2. Employee Guide

Employees use the platform to customize their digital profiles, track their daily scan goals, and view their leaderboard rankings.

### 2.1 Registration & Login
1. If you don't have an account, navigate to the platform URL and click **Create one free**.
2. Fill in your details (Username, Email, Business Name, Password).
3. Once registered, log in to access your Employee Dashboard.

### 2.2 Profile Customization
1. Click **Profile & Template** in the sidebar.
2. Fill out your professional details (Name, Bio, Phone, Address, Social Links).
3. These details will be displayed on your public digital profile when someone taps your physical NFC card.

### 2.3 Your Digital ID Card
1. Click **My ID Card** in the sidebar.
2. This displays your official digital identity card, including your Employee ID, organization name, and contact info. 
3. A progress bar shows how complete your profile is. Ensure it reaches 100% by filling out all details in the Profile section.

### 2.4 Tracking Goals & Leaderboard
1. **Daily Goals:** Click **Daily Goals** to view today's target (e.g., "0 / 20 unique scans"). As you tap your card with new clients, this progress bar will fill up. *Note: Only one tap per IP address per day counts towards your goal.*
2. **Leaderboard:** Click **Leaderboard** to see how you rank against other employees based on weekly scan activity. The top 3 employees are highlighted on the podium.

### 2.5 Inbox
1. Click **Inbox** to view announcements sent by the Administrator.

---

## 3. NFC Card Programming Guide

To link a physical NFC card to an employee's digital profile, you must program the card with a specific URL.

### Requirements:
- A blank, rewritable NFC card (e.g., NTAG215).
- An NFC-enabled smartphone (iOS or Android).
- The free **NFC Tools** app (available on the App Store and Google Play).

### Step-by-Step Programming:
1. **Find the Target URL:**
   - As an admin, assign a card slug (unique ID) to the employee in the **User Control** panel (e.g., `john-doe`).
   - The target URL for programming will be: `https://your-domain.com/t/john-doe` *(Replace `your-domain.com` with your actual live server domain).*
2. **Open NFC Tools:**
   - Launch the **NFC Tools** app on your smartphone.
3. **Write the URL:**
   - Tap on **Write**.
   - Tap on **Add a record**.
   - Select **URL / URI**.
   - Enter the target URL (e.g., `https://your-domain.com/t/john-doe`). Ensure you include the `https://` prefix.
   - Tap **OK**.
4. **Program the Card:**
   - Tap **Write / 30 Bytes** (the byte size will vary depending on URL length).
   - The app will display a prompt saying "Approach an NFC tag".
   - Hold the physical NFC card against the back of your smartphone (near the top for iPhones, middle/top for Androids).
   - Wait for the success checkmark.
5. **Test the Card:**
   - Tap the card against your phone again (outside of the NFC Tools app).
   - Your web browser should open, redirect through the tracking link, and land on the employee's digital profile.

> [!IMPORTANT] 
> **Testing Tip:** If you test the card multiple times from the same phone/Wi-Fi, only the first tap of the day will award gamification points due to the platform's anti-spam (unique IP) tracking.

---
*End of Manual*
